# using_redis_search

## Client-Facing API Endpoints

### Search & Autocomplete

#### `GET /api/autocomplete`

JSON autocomplete for the search input. Returns categorized results from all or selected sources.

| Param | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `q` | string | yes | — | Search query (min 2 chars) |
| `sources` | string | no | all | Comma-separated: tv, movie, person, podcast, author, book, news, video, ratings, artist, album |
| `raw` | bool | no | false | Treat `q` as raw RediSearch syntax for indexed sources |
| `no_duplicate` | bool | no | false | Exclude exact match item from its source results list |
| `full` | bool | no | false | Fetch 250 media candidates instead of 50 for deeper ranking |

Response: `{ movie: [...], tv: [...], person: [...], ... , exact_match: {...} }` keyed by source.

Supports source hints in the query (e.g. `movie: matrix`). Returns `source_hint` in response when detected.

#### `GET /api/autocomplete/minimal`

Lightweight projected autocomplete optimised for speed.  Uses Redis `RETURN` field projection so only the requested properties are transferred from the index.  No brokered API calls, no full-document parsing, no Python re-ranking.

| Param | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `q` | string | yes | — | Search query (min 2 chars) |
| `sources` | string | no | tv,movie | Comma-separated indexed sources: tv, movie, person, podcast, author, book |
| `limit` | int | no | 10 | Max results per source (1–50) |
| `fields` | string | no | default set | Comma-separated field names to return. `mc_id`, `mc_type` always included. |

Default fields: `mc_id`, `mc_type`, `search_title`, `year`, `poster_path`, `popularity`, `image`.

Response: `{ "tv": [...], "movie": [...], ... }` keyed by source.  Each item contains only the projected fields.

#### `GET /api/autocomplete/stream`

SSE streaming version of autocomplete. Same parameters as above. Results stream as each source completes.

SSE events:
- `event: result` → `{ source, results, latency_ms }`
- `event: exact_match` → provisional exact match
- `event: exact_match_final` → authoritative exact match
- `event: done` → all sources complete

#### `GET /api/search`

Unified multi-source search with filtering. Supports both text queries and field-only browse.

| Param | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `q` | string | no | — | Search query (optional if filters provided) |
| `sources` | string | no | all | Comma-separated source list |
| `limit` | int | no | 10 | Max results per source (1–50) |
| `genre_ids` | string | no | — | Comma-separated TMDB genre IDs |
| `genre_match` | string | no | `any` | `any` (OR) or `all` (AND) |
| `cast_ids` | string | no | — | Comma-separated TMDB person IDs |
| `cast_match` | string | no | `any` | `any` (OR) or `all` (AND) |
| `year_min` | int | no | — | Minimum release year |
| `year_max` | int | no | — | Maximum release year |
| `rating_min` | float | no | — | Minimum rating (0–10) |
| `rating_max` | float | no | — | Maximum rating (0–10) |
| `mc_type` | string | no | — | Filter by: `movie` or `tv` |
| `ratings_sort` | string | no | `popularity` | Sort for ratings source: `popularity`, `audience_score`, `critics_score` |
| `raw` | bool | no | false | Treat `q` as raw RediSearch syntax |
| `no_duplicate` | bool | no | false | Exclude exact match from source list |
| `full` | bool | no | false | Deep ranking mode (250 candidates) |

Sources: Indexed (tv, movie, person, podcast, author, book) support field-only filtering. Brokered (artist, album, video, news, ratings) require a text query. Ratings can be enriched from indexed tv/movie results when requested together.

Response: `{ movie: [...], tv: [...], person: [...], ... , exact_match: {...} }` keyed by source.

#### `GET /api/search/stream`

SSE streaming version of `/api/search`. Same parameters. Same SSE event format as autocomplete/stream.

#### `GET /api/resolve`

Resolve a fully-formed title to all exact-match (tier 0-1) entities. Unlike `/api/autocomplete` which returns a single `exact_match` winner, this returns every qualifying match ranked by popularity/recency.

When `near_misses` > 0 and no exact matches are found, the top N best-ranked non-exact candidates are returned in a `near_misses` key, enabling "Did you mean?" fallback UX.

| Param | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `q` | string | yes | — | Fully-formed title (min 2 chars) |
| `sources` | string | no | tv,movie | Comma-separated indexed sources: tv, movie, person, podcast, author, book |
| `fields` | string | no | default set | Extra field names to include per match. Ignored when `full=true`. |
| `full` | bool | no | false | Return the complete Redis document for each match |
| `near_misses` | int | no | 0 | When > 0 and no exact matches found, return up to N best-ranked near-miss candidates. Range: 0–10. |

Default fields (always included): `mc_id`, `mc_type`, `title`, `search_title`, `release_date`, `first_air_date`, `last_aired_date`.

Allowed extra fields: same allowlist as `/api/autocomplete/minimal`.

Response:

```json
{
  "query": "The Godfather",
  "matches": [
    { "mc_id": "tmdb_238", "mc_type": "movie", "title": "The Godfather", ... },
    { "mc_id": "tmdb_240", "mc_type": "movie", "title": "The Godfather Part II", ... }
  ],
  "near_misses": [],
  "total": 2,
  "latency_ms": 12.3
}
```

Near-miss fallback (no exact matches, `near_misses=2`):

```json
{
  "query": "Godfater",
  "matches": [],
  "near_misses": [
    { "mc_id": "tmdb_238", "mc_type": "movie", "source": "movie", "search_title": "The Godfather", ... },
    { "mc_id": "tmdb_240", "mc_type": "movie", "source": "movie", "search_title": "The Godfather Part II", ... }
  ],
  "total": 0,
  "latency_ms": 14.1
}
```

Key differences from autocomplete/search:
- Returns a flat `matches` array, not grouped by source.
- Returns **all** exact matches, not just one `exact_match` winner.
- Only indexed sources (no brokered APIs).
- Supports `full=true` for complete Redis documents.
- Supports `near_misses` for fallback suggestions when no exact match is found.

### Detail Lookups

#### `POST /api/details`

Multi-type detail lookup by `mc_id`. Documented in detail below under "Detail Lookup Endpoint".

#### `GET /api/media/{media_id}`

Get a single media document from Redis by ID. Returns the full Redis JSON doc.

| Param | Type | Required | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| `media_id` | path | yes | Media ID (e.g. `tmdb_movie_550` or `media:tmdb_movie_550`) |

Response: `{ id, mc_id, title, ... }` (full Redis document). 404 if not found.

#### `PUT /api/media/{media_id}`

Update a Redis media document. Merges provided fields into existing doc. Immutable fields (`id`, `mc_id`, `source`, `source_id`, `mc_type`) cannot be changed.

Request body:

```json
{
  "document": { "field": "new_value" },
  "push_to_media_manager": true,
  "metadata_only": false
}
```

Response: `{ status: "updated", id, media_manager: {...}, document: {...} }`

#### `GET /api/media-details`

Return the Redis document for a media item. On cache miss with `allow_insert=true` or `force_refresh=true`, fetches from TMDB, normalizes, writes to Redis, and returns the document.

| Param | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `mc_id` | string | yes | — | MediaCircle ID (e.g. `tmdb_movie_550`) |
| `allow_insert` | bool | no | false | Allow TMDB fetch + Redis write on cache miss |
| `force_refresh` | bool | no | false | Skip Redis cache, always fetch from TMDB |

Response: Redis document shape. Note: `allow_insert` and `force_refresh` cause a write side effect.

#### `GET /api/cast-names`

Get cast names for a movie/TV show with names split into first/last parts. Search by title or provide a direct TMDB ID.

| Param | Type | Required | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| `query` | string | no | Title to search for |
| `tmdb_id` | int | no | Direct TMDB ID (bypasses search) |
| `media_type` | string | no | `movie` or `tv` (default: search both) |

One of `query` or `tmdb_id` is required.

Response: `{ title, description, cast_names: [{ first, last, character_first, character_last }] }`

#### `GET /api/news/reviews`

Get recent news/reviews for a movie or TV show via NewsAI.

| Param | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `title` | string | yes | — | Title of the movie/TV show |
| `media_type` | string | no | `tv` | `movie` or `tv` |
| `page_size` | int | no | 10 | Number of articles (1–50) |

#### `GET /api/changes`

Return documents modified in a time range across one or more indexes. Used for sync/replication.

| Param | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `since` | int | yes | — | Inclusive start (Unix timestamp) |
| `until` | int | no | +inf | Inclusive end (Unix timestamp) |
| `sources` | string | no | all | Comma-separated: media, people, podcast, book, author |
| `start` | int | no | 0 | Pagination offset per source |
| `take` | int | no | 100 | Page size per source (1–1000) |
| `change_source` | string | no | — | Filter by `_source` field value (e.g. `backfill`) |

Response:

```json
{
  "since": 1710000000,
  "until": null,
  "start": 0,
  "take": 100,
  "sources": ["media", "people"],
  "results": {
    "media": { "count": 50, "total": 1200, "next_start": 100, "items": [...] },
    "people": { "count": 30, "total": 30, "items": [...] }
  }
}
```

