## TMDB Web UI Behavior

### Toggle

The TMDB toggle switch in the search bar controls TMDB mode:

- **ON**: Autocomplete and regular index search are suppressed. Enter triggers `searchTmdb()` → `GET /api/tmdb/search?mode=redis`.
- **OFF**: Normal autocomplete and multi-source search resume.

Toggle state is checked by `search-controller.js` via the `isTmdbModeEnabled` callback.

### Buttons — TMDB search results

| Button | Action | Endpoint |
|--------|--------|----------|
| **Redis Doc** | Display in-memory normalized Redis document (no API call) | — |
| **MC Item** | Fetch MC model payload on-demand | `GET /api/tmdb/details?mode=mc_item` |
| **TMDB** | Fetch raw TMDB data on-demand | `GET /api/tmdb/details?mode=tmdb` |
| **ADD TO REDIS** (orange) | Write to Redis — shown when `_exists_in_redis` is false | `POST /api/tmdb/add-to-redis` |
| **UPDATE REDIS DOC** (green) | Write to Redis — shown when `_exists_in_redis` is true | `POST /api/tmdb/add-to-redis` |

### Buttons — regular index results

| Button | Action |
|--------|--------|
| **Redis Doc** | Display the in-memory search result |
| **View Media Details** | Read-only fetch from `/api/media-details` (no write) |
